      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/66/1386",
      "text": [
        " اَللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ «لاٰ تَقْرَبُوا اَلصَّلاٰةَ وَ أَنْتُمْ سُكٰارىٰ حَتّٰى تَعْلَمُوا مٰا تَقُولُونَ»\nقَالَ «مِنْهُ سُكْرُ اَلنَّوْمِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1386 - Zakariyya al-Naqqad reported from Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) regarding the words of Allah (swt), the Mighty and Majestic:\n\"Do not approach prayer while you are intoxicated until you know what you are saying\" (Surah An-Nisa 4:43).\nImam (as) said: \"This includes the intoxication of sleep.\""
        ]
      }
    },
